Namibia Plans to Introduce Capital Gains Tax on Mine Changes, NBC Reports

-- B y   C h a m w e   K a i r a
-- 
2011-06-23T10:05:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/namibia-plans-to-introduce-capital-gains-tax-on-mine-changes-nbc-reports.html
Namibia  plans to introduce a capital
gains tax for changes of ownership of mining companies, the
country’s state-controlled broadcaster reported, citing Finance
Minister Saara Kuugongelwa-Amadhila.  The proposal is part of a new tax bill approved by the
southern African nation’s cabinet, Windhoek-based Namibia
Broadcasting Corp. cited Kuugongelwa-Amadhila as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chamwe Kaira in Windhoek at 
 ckaira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
